snippet.textDisplay:
I feel that in order to not disrupt essential supply chain and infrastructure the government must...

Encourage employees call in to work to enquire if necessary to come in....

And tell employees that they must keep reporting to work until employer tells them not to.


****


Many people work in industries that are an essential part of infrastructure or supply chain, a part which may not be obvious.

Folks who are otherwise quite healthy (another reason for Covid testing to be in plentiful supply) just cannot call in saying they are being required by government entities to shelter in place and so won’t be coming in to work.

For example:

If that person is the guy that runs the machine that makes the plastic pellets that go to mfrs of ventilators then that part of supply chain may just shut down.

Employers in less essential businesses can voluntarily downsize their workforce (or be officially encouraged to do so).

Other employers whose part in essential supply chain may be unclear can lay off workers but must also be encouraged to tell their people to shelter in place, stay healthy and be ready to return to work in short order when called.

Covid testing with timely test results must be readily available for those still employed as well as for those who must return to work.

This may be reason some officials are not declaring total shutdown and enforced quarantine of their cities.



So, as a government or health official:

We must....

not cause shutdown of supply chain and infrastructure by declaring a total quarantine of cities and regions that would prevent essential persons from going to work.

And


We must....

continue to vastly increase testing capability (with minimal delay in obtaining results) to keep essential workforce in place.


If all this this sounds reasonable to those reading this comment, please, in addition to pressing the ‘like’ button, you must forward copy to your govt representative.
